    "description": "Nippon Carbide Industries Co., Inc. engages in the electronic and functional products, and films and sheetings business in Japan, Asia, and internationally. The company offers functional chemicals, such as electronic materials, coating materials, agrochemicals, metal surface treatment agents, pharmaceutical products, and biochemistry; and functional polymers, including thickening and adhesive agents, resin for dyes and coating materials, and melamine resin for tableware, as well as treating fibers, paper, etc. It also provides semiconductor mold cleaners and conditioners; and ceramic substrates, such as alumina substrates, thick-film printing substrates, and green sheetings. In addition, it offers marking films, laser markable labels, and packaging materials; graphic and 3D-emblem stickers; retroreflective sheetings, aluminum connected sign substrates, and aerial display reflectors. Nippon Carbide Industries Co., Inc. was incorporated in 1935 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan."
